result.execSummary:
This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Alexis M Jordan appeared by video.  Attorney Sylvan Jaspen appeared by video on behalf of Attorney Michael V Fuentes for Alexis M Jordan.  Attorney James C Griffin in court for State of Wisconsin.

Case in court for a status conference.  Defense acknowledges receipt of discovery but no offer and requests another status date.  State has no objection to an adjournment.  Court scheduled the matter as requested.  Court approves Zoom appearances at the next court date.  Case adjourned to Branch 2, Rm 635 CH.
Status conference scheduled for November 17, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Alexis M Jordan appeared by video.  Attorney Michael J Cerniglia appeared by video for Alexis M Jordan.  Prosecuting attorney James C Griffin in court for the State of Wisconsin. Status conference held. Counsel informed Court there has been a breakdown in communication.  Defense motion to withdraw as counsel is granted by the court. Defense counsel will notify Public Defender's Office to appoint new counsel for the defendant.  Case adjourned for status of counsel in Branch 02.
Status conference scheduled for October 19, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

Defendant Alexis M Jordan in court, appear by video with attorney Michael J Cerniglia, appear by video.  Gregg Herman appeared in person for the State of Wisconsin.
  Preliminary hearing proceeded.  Sworn for the State: Brown Deer Police Officer W. Wandaogo.   State rests.  Defense rests.  Defense motion to dismiss argued and denied. Court found probable cause and bound defendant over for trial.  Original information received and filed;  defendant given a copy, waived reading, was arraigned in open court and plead not guilty.  Case is adjourned to Branch 02.  Scheduling conference scheduled for September 13, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
COURT ORDERED DEFENDANT TO REPORT TO THE MILWAUKEE COUNTY JAIL (CJF) TO BE BOOKED AND RELEASED BY 5:00 P.M. ON 07-14-2022. IF THEY FAIL TO APPEAR, A BENCH WARRANT WILL BE ISSUED FOR THEIR ARREST.

Defendant Alexis M Jordan in court with attorney Colin Patrick McGinn.  Jon R Josephsen appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Defendant given a copy of complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  Court reviewed complaint and found probable cause to hold defendant for further proceedings.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND PUBLIC DEFENDER WILL PROVIDE COUNSEL.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Childs, Branch 2.  Case is adjourned for preliminary hearing in Branch PE.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for July 25, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Summons mailed.  Defendant ordered into room 221 Safety Building on 7/12/22 @ 1p
